---
/**
 * Players Guide - Jobs & Economy
 */
import GuideLayout from '../../layouts/GuideLayout.astro';
---

<GuideLayout title="Jobs & Economy" currentPage="economy" description="Learn about BlockHaven's job system and player economy">
  <h1>Jobs & Economy</h1>
  <p class="text-xl !text-text-light mb-8">
    Earn money by doing what you love! BlockHaven features a full economy system with jobs, trading, and more.
  </p>

  <section id="overview">
    <h2>How the Economy Works</h2>
    <p>
      On BlockHaven, you earn money by joining jobs and performing activities related to that job.
      Money can be used to trade with other players, buy items from shops, and more.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-primary-gold/10 border border-primary-gold/30 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="!mt-0 !text-primary-gold">Getting Started</h4>
      <p class="!mb-0">
        Check your current balance anytime with <code>/bal</code> or <code>/balance</code>.
        To see the wealthiest players on the server, use <code>/baltop</code>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="jobs">
    <h2>Jobs System</h2>
    <p>
      Jobs let you earn money by doing everyday Minecraft activities. The more you work,
      the more you earn - and you level up to increase your pay rate!
    </p>

    <h3>Available Jobs</h3>
    <p>Browse available jobs with <code>/jobs browse</code>. Here are some of the jobs you can join:</p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-secondary-stone/10 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Miner</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Earn money by mining ores and stone</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-secondary-stone/10 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Woodcutter</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Earn money by chopping down trees</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-secondary-stone/10 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Farmer</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Earn money by growing and harvesting crops</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-secondary-stone/10 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Hunter</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Earn money by hunting mobs and animals</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-secondary-stone/10 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Fisherman</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Earn money by fishing</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-secondary-stone/10 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Builder</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Earn money by placing blocks</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-secondary-stone/10 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Digger</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Earn money by digging dirt, sand, and gravel</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-secondary-stone/10 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Crafter</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Earn money by crafting items</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-secondary-stone/10 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Enchanter</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Earn money by enchanting items</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Joining a Job</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Type <code>/jobs browse</code> to see all available jobs</li>
      <li>Click on a job to see what activities pay and how much</li>
      <li>Type <code>/jobs join [jobname]</code> to join that job</li>
      <li>Start performing activities to earn money!</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="bg-accent-diamond/10 border border-accent-diamond/30 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="!mt-0 text-accent-diamond">Multiple Jobs</h4>
      <p class="!mb-0">
        You can join multiple jobs at once! This lets you earn money from different activities.
        Use <code>/jobs leave [jobname]</code> to leave a job if you want to try something different.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="leveling">
    <h2>Job Leveling</h2>
    <p>
      As you work in a job, you earn experience and level up. Higher levels mean:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Better pay</strong> - Each level increases your earnings</li>
      <li><strong>Increased experience</strong> - Level up faster as you progress</li>
      <li><strong>Recognition</strong> - Show off your dedication!</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Checking Your Progress</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Command</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/jobs stats</code></td>
          <td>See your level and experience in all jobs</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/jobs info [job]</code></td>
          <td>Detailed info about a specific job's pay rates</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/jobs top [job]</code></td>
          <td>See the top players in a specific job</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section id="trading">
    <h2>Trading with Players</h2>
    <p>
      The player-to-player economy is a great way to get items you need and sell things you have extra of.
    </p>

    <h3>Sending Money</h3>
    <p>
      Use <code>/pay [player] [amount]</code> to send money to another player.
      For example, <code>/pay Steve 100</code> sends $100 to Steve.
    </p>

    <h3>Trading Tips</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Agree on terms first</strong> - Discuss what you're trading in chat before exchanging</li>
      <li><strong>Use a safe location</strong> - Trade in a public area or your claimed land</li>
      <li><strong>Build trust</strong> - Start with small trades before big ones</li>
      <li><strong>Be fair</strong> - Ripping off other players is against our community spirit</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="job-commands">
    <h2>All Jobs Commands</h2>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Command</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/jobs browse</code></td>
          <td>Browse all available jobs</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/jobs join [job]</code></td>
          <td>Join a job</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/jobs leave [job]</code></td>
          <td>Leave a job</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/jobs stats</code></td>
          <td>View your job stats and levels</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/jobs info [job]</code></td>
          <td>View detailed info about a job</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/jobs top [job]</code></td>
          <td>View top players in a job</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/jobs leaveall</code></td>
          <td>Leave all jobs</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section id="economy-commands">
    <h2>Economy Commands</h2>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Command</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/bal</code> or <code>/balance</code></td>
          <td>Check your current balance</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/baltop</code></td>
          <td>See the richest players on the server</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>/pay [player] [amount]</code></td>
          <td>Send money to another player</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section id="tips">
    <h2>Tips for Earning Money</h2>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Choose complementary jobs</strong> - Join jobs that match your playstyle. If you love mining, join Miner!</li>
      <li><strong>Level up consistently</strong> - Focus on a few jobs rather than spreading thin across many</li>
      <li><strong>Combine activities</strong> - A Farmer who also joins Crafter earns money growing wheat AND making bread</li>
      <li><strong>Stay active</strong> - Earnings come from actually doing activities, so keep playing!</li>
      <li><strong>Check pay rates</strong> - Some activities pay more than others. Use <code>/jobs info</code> to see specifics</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="next-steps">
    <h2>Next Steps</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-6">
      <a href="/guide/worlds" class="block bg-secondary-stone/10 hover:bg-secondary-stone/20 rounded-xl p-6 transition-colors no-underline">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Worlds & Travel</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Learn about different worlds and how to travel between them.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/guide/land-claims" class="block bg-secondary-stone/10 hover:bg-secondary-stone/20 rounded-xl p-6 transition-colors no-underline">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-text-light mb-2">Land Claims</h4>
        <p class="text-sm !mb-0">Protect your base and builds from other players.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</GuideLayout>
